      • addBusCentres

        public void addBusCentres(java.lang.CharSequence param)
        Appends the specified BusCentres to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Multi-valued field containing a list of the countries to be used when calculating the value date to be used forcorporate actions for this security. See the helptext for the DAY.CONVENTION field for the rules used by T24 whencalculating a working day for the value date. Any input must exist on the COUNTRY file. A particular country can only be entered once. Will default to thecountry input into the COMPANY.DOMICILE field if no input has been made. Validation Rules: Any input must be a valid COUNTRY code. Will default to the COUNTRY code input in the COMPANY.DOMICILE field. Duplicate Country Codes are not allowed.

        Parameters:
        param - the BusCentres to append
        Returns:
        nothing

      • addBusCentres

        public void addBusCentres(TField param)
        Appends the specified BusCentres to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Multi-valued field containing a list of the countries to be used when calculating the value date to be used forcorporate actions for this security. See the helptext for the DAY.CONVENTION field for the rules used by T24 whencalculating a working day for the value date. Any input must exist on the COUNTRY file. A particular country can only be entered once. Will default to thecountry input into the COMPANY.DOMICILE field if no input has been made. Validation Rules: Any input must be a valid COUNTRY code. Will default to the COUNTRY code input in the COMPANY.DOMICILE field. Duplicate Country Codes are not allowed.

        Field description: This input for this field is determined in the application SM.PARAMETER, if the field PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is notSWIFT then the only valid input for this field is xd, otherwise the list of valid entries will be determined fromthe fields CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE in the same application. If the entry is xd then it indicates that the price quoted in the LAST.PRICE or DISC.YLD.PERC field isex-dividend. Otherwise it indicates the price condition, as specified by SWIFT, for example CDIV indicates the price is cumdividend, XWAR indicates the price is ex warrants. The user should consult the SWIFT manual for a full list ofprice conditions. Validation Rules: Input only allowed if the security price is updated manually otherwise this field is updated by the externalprice field. If PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is not SWIFT then the only permissible input is xd (Lowercase only - UPPERCASE not allowed) If PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is SWIFT then entry will be limited to values from CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE onSM.PARAMETER.

      • getAdjMarginRate

        public TField getAdjMarginRate()
        Returns the AdjMarginRate

        Field description: This field is used to specify the Adjusted margin rate for calculating ADJ.MARGIN.AMT in SC.POS.ASSET. Adjusted Margin Rate is used to calculate the Low Advanced Ratio for Collaterals to which the Portfolio/Asset isattached. Low Advance Ratio is the percentage of collateral that will be used for allocating to other currency liabilitiesduring collateral deficit calculation in Advance Collateral process. This field can either be used to specify the Low Advance Ratio for collateral LTV calculation or DiversifiedMargins for porfolios flagged for Diversification. If the flag "CO.MV.CHECK" in SC.PARAMETER is set to enable Preferential LTV functionality, Adj Marginwill be used only as Low Advance Ratio for collateral LTV calculations and will not be used for calculatingDiversified Margin. In this case ideally Adj Margin should be lesser than the Margin Rate. Thus an override will be raised if AdjMargin is greater than Preferential Margin Rate/Standard Margin Rate. a. If ADJ.MARGIN.RATE is used for diversification purpose and bank wants to use both concentration and portfoliodiversification functionality then, it will require a process change configurationso as to setup and use ADJ.MARGIN.RATE for concentration and PREFNTL.MARGIN.RATE for diversification and also set thefield CO.MV.CHECK in SC.PARAMETER as YES. b. If ADJ.MARGIN.RATE is used for concentration purpose and bank wants to use portfolio diversificationfunctionality then, it will require configuring field CO.MV.CHECK in SC.PARAMETER as YESand setup PREFNTL.MARGIN.RATE to be used for diversification. Validation Rules: Standard T24 Rate field with values ranging from 0 to 100.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The AdjMarginRate

        Field description: This field is used by AM.MODELLING during Rebalance process. but in the event that the underlying security may be traded in fractions, then this field should be used tospecify the number of decimals permissable. 1 to indicate that only whole numbers are allowable. 0 to indicate any amount of decimals up to and including 6 (therefore same as 0.000001) 0.1 only one decimal permitted (can be none) 0.01 up to and including 2 decimals (none, 1 and 2) 0.001 up to and including 3 decimals (none, 1, 2 and 3) 0.0001 up to and including 4 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3 and 4) 0.00001 up to and including 5 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5) 0.000001 up to and including 6 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6) A setting of 0.001 means that the underlying security may be traded, for example, 123.1 or 123.12 or 123.123 butnot 123.1234. Validation Rules: Non Mandatory AM.TRADING.UNITS should be a Multiple of ODD.LOT.UNITS.

      • getDayConvention

        public TField getDayConvention()
        Returns the DayConvention

        Field description: Day convention to be used when calculating the Value Date for any corporate actions for this security. This isthe convention to be used when finding a working day in all the countries listed in the BUS.CENTRES field. This field will be used by the applications DIARY, DIV.COUP.DET, REDEMPTION.DET and STOCK.DIV.DET to calculate aworking day value date from the defaulted value date of the corporate actions event if this defaulted date is anon-working day in all the countries listed in the BUS.CENTRES field. Optional field. Any input must be FOLLOWING, MODIFIED or PRECEDING. These inputs have the following meanings; FOLLOWING The value date will be the first working day that follows the defaulted date. PRECEDING The value date will be the first working day that precedes the defaulted date. MODIFIED The value date will be the first working day that follows the defaulted day unless it falls in the nextcalendar month, in which case the value date will be the first working day that precedes the defaulted date. If this field is left blank then the value date used will be the defaulted date. Validation Rules: Optional input. Any input must be FOLLOWING, MODIFIED or PRECEDING.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The DayConvention

      • getEntryLoadMethod

        public TField getEntryLoadMethod()
        Returns the EntryLoadMethod

        Field description: The field identifies how the entry load is calculated and handled. There are different options as shown below:BID.OFFER - Denotes the entry load is factored into the NAV (Offer Price). Entry load need not be calculatedseparately.BANKPL - The entry load is calculated and only the net amount (after adjusting the entry load) is remitted to the fundhouse. The entry load will be booked to bank's PL.NETAMT - The fund house will calculate the entry load and allocate units for the net amount (subscription amount - entryload). The entry load may fully or partially be shared with the distributor separately. If Blank , then value will be defaulted from ENTRY.LOAD.METHOD in SC.STD.SEC.TRADE.The default method will beBANKPL Validation Rules: Allowed Values:BID.OFFER,NETAMT,BANKPL

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The EntryLoadMethod

      • getFifWeight

        public TField getFifWeight()
        Returns the FifWeight

        Field description: The Foreign Inclusion Factor (FIF) of an instrument is a weighting assigned to an instrument that represents theproportion of shares outstanding that are deemed to be available for purchase in the public equity markets byinternational investors. In practice limitations on availability include: strategic and other shareholdings in an instrument limits on foreign ownership. The FIF is used by companies who compile indexes to provide a more accurate representation of company weightingin the index calculation. The contents of this field will be used by the AM.BENCH.INDICES application to provide amore accurate methodology of calculating indices. (NOT CURRENTLY DEVELOPED) A value between 0 and 1 should be entered.

      • getGrp1Grp2Method

        public TField getGrp1Grp2Method()
        Returns the Grp1Grp2Method

        Field description: The system calculates Group 1 holdings as at the start of the Equalisation Period (date of last unit trustdistribution). All purchases from this date up until the end of the equalization period (ex-date) will be classedas Group 2 holdings. This field dictates which Group (1 or 2) sales will be deducted from during the Equalisation Period. null - The SUMLIFO option is used FIFO - Uses the First In/First Out calculation for sales LIFO - Uses Last In /First Out calculation for sales SUMLIFO - Sums all the purchases sales then performs Last In/First Out Calculation for the result DEFAULT - Copies the default setting from the SUB.ASSET.TYPE record Validation Rules: LIFO, FIFO, SUMLIFO or DEFAULT Examples 1. In this example the first transaction we have is a sale followed by a purchase. FIFO This method will try reduce the Group 1 units first but if there is not enough Group 1 units, the remainder willbe taken from Group 2 units.

        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000 0 8,000
        Purchase5,000 8,000 5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 6,500 5,000 11,500
        Total 6,500 5,000 11,500
        LIFO This method will try reduce the Group 2 units first but if there is not enough Group 2 units, the remainder willbe taken from Group 1 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000 0 8,000
        Purchase5,000 8,000 5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 8,000 3,500 11,500
        Total 8,000 3,500 11,500
        SUMLIFO This method will sum all the purchase sales for the Equalisation Period then try to reduce the Group 2 unitsfirst but if there is not enough Group 2 units, the remainder will be taken from Group 1 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000
        Purchase5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 11,500
        Total(1,500) 10,000 1,500 11,500
        2. In this example the first transaction is a purchase followed by two sales. This method will try reduce the Group 1 units first but if there is not enough Group 1 units, the remainder willbe taken from Group 2 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Purchase5,000 10,000 5,000 15,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000 5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 6,500 5,000 11,500
        Total 6,500 5,000 11,500
        LIFO This method will try reduce the Group 2 units first but if there is not enough Group 2 units, the remainder willbe taken from Group 1 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Purchase5,000 10,000 5,000 15,000
        Sale-2,000 10,000 3,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 10,000 1,500 11,500
        Total 10,000 1,500 11,500
        SUMLIFO This method will sum all the purchase sales for the Equalisation Period then try to reduce the Group 2 unitsfirst but if there is not enough Group 2 units, the remainder will be taken from Group 1 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000
        Purchase5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 11,500
        Total(1,500) 10,000 1,500 11,500

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The Grp1Grp2Method

      • getInterestDayBasis

        public TField getInterestDayBasis()
        Returns the InterestDayBasis

        Field description: Defines the method of calculation for accrued interest on a Security be it a Bond, Gilt, Loan stock etc. Example: A = 360/360 where a standard 30 day month is assumed over 360 days a year, as is the case for allEurobond calculations. Note that O and U values are intended to enable the setting-up of French Oat and US Treasury Bills respectively. For US Treasury (value = U), the number of days in the denominator vary according to the number of days in theinterest period. For example, if the number of days in the interest period is 182 and the number of payments in ayear is 2, then the denominator (i.e. basis days) would be 364. Similarly, if number of days in a interest periodis 184, the base days would be 368. For a basic fixed interest French Oat (value = O) and also for French BTAN issues, the process requires roundingwithin the calculation to the nearest THIRD decimal (0.0005 is rounded up) For example : An investor holds 10 000 securities of the 5.25%, 25 April 2008, OAT. Full coupon per security: 0.05250 payable on 25 April 2000 Accrued interest calculation date: 24 March 2000 Number of days accrued: 334 Total number of days in the interest period: 366 (the O is actually hard-coded as ACT/ACT basis) Calculation : 5.25 * 334 / 366 = 4.790834 rounded to 3 decimals = 4.791 Therefore : Accrued interest in percentage: 4.791% Total amount of accrued interest paid in euro: 479.10 NOTE : Please refer to the BOND.ROUNDING field on this file, the two files UNIT.INT.METHOD and BOND.ROUNDING to enablegreater control over rounding of interest. Your User Guide explains the processes in greater detail to help youdecide. Validation Rules: Alphabetic character. (Optional input) If BOND.OR.SHARE is B input is mandatory, regardless of whether an interest rate is specified. If left blank anunreliable yield figure will be calculated. If BOND.OR.SHARE is S input is not allowed. Only A, B, C, D, E, F, G, O or U can be entered into this field. If G is entered then the NO.OF.PAYMENTS field must be either 1, 2, 4, 13, 26 or 52.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The InterestDayBasis

        Field description: This field accepts either five alpha characters or ID of existing PERIODIC.INTEREST table.         Parameters:
        Returns:

        Field description: Specifies the enhanced margin rate that will override any standard margin (MARGIN.RATE) applicable for portfoliosflagged for Diversification. Validation Rules: Standard T24 Rate field. This field is allowed for input only when "CO.MV.CHECK" flag in SC.PARAMETER is set that enables thePreferential LTV functionality. Value can be specified as an absolute value ranging from 0 to 100 or as a variance with "+" sign. A variance indicates the incremental value to be added to the Standrad Margin Rate to arrive at the enhancedrate. Thus Margin Rate becomes mandatory if Preferential Rate is defined as a variance. The sum of Preferential Rate defined as a variance and Standard Margin Rate cannot exceed 100. Ideally Preferential Rate should always be greater than the Standard Margin Rate. Thus an override will be raisedif the Preferential Rate defined as an absolute value is lesser than the Standard Margin Rate. The hierarchy in which the Preferential Rate will be considered is the same as existing margin rate determinationhierarchy.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The PrefntlMarginRate

        Field description: This input for this field is determined in the application SM.PARAMETER, if the field PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is notSWIFT then the only valid input for this field is xd, otherwise the list of valid entries will be determined fromthe fields CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE in the same application. If the entry is xd then it indicates that the price quoted in the LAST.PRICE or DISC.YLD.PERC field isex-dividend. Otherwise it indicates the price condition, as specified by SWIFT, for example CDIV indicates the price is cumdividend, XWAR indicates the price is ex warrants. The user should consult the SWIFT manual for a full list ofprice conditions. Validation Rules: Input only allowed if the security price is updated manually otherwise this field is updated by the externalprice field. If PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is not SWIFT then the only permissible input is xd (Lowercase only - UPPERCASE not allowed) If PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is SWIFT then entry will be limited to values from CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE onSM.PARAMETER.

        public TField getSecStatus()

        Field description: DEF - Defaulted ,mainly for bonds where coupon payment is defaulted. Trading can still continue. No overridemessage or hard block by the system DEL - Delisted ,when security is delisted from exchange, it is also expired and no more trading can be done for this security. System will raise an override message, validating against the status date for any transactionson or after the status date SUS - Suspended , when security is suspended with an effective date, no more trading is allowed. System should provide an override message, validating against the status date for any transactions on or after thestatus date. NON.TRADABLE - When security is Non Tradable with an effective date, no more trading is allowed.         Returns the SubAmtAdj

        Field description: In cases where rebate or discount is offered on the entry load, this field determines whether the clientinvestment (subscription amount) will be retained or reduced based on the rebate/discount offered. If the field is No or blank, the original subscription amount will be retained (by grossing up the investmentamount) and client will be debited for the same after applying the rebate (and channel discount) on entry load. If set to YES, the subscription amount will be reduced in line with rebate/channel discount. The field atSECURITY.MASTER level will override the company level setting. Validation Rules: Allowed Values:YES, NO or blank

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The SubAmtAdj

      • getTradingUnits

        public TField getTradingUnits()
        Returns the TradingUnits

        Field description: Specifies the smallest nominal amount that may be traded. Normally, for share type securities this will default to 1 but in the event that the underlying security may betraded in fractions, then this field should be used to specify the number of decimals permissable. 1 to indicate that only whole numbers are allowable. 0 to indicate any amount of decimals up to and including 6 (therefore same as 0.000001) 0.1 only one decimal permitted (can be none) 0.01 up to and including 2 decimals (none, 1 and 2) 0.001 up to and including 3 decimals (none, 1, 2 and 3) 0.0001 up to and including 4 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3 and 4) 0.00001 up to and including 5 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5) 0.000001 up to and including 6 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6) A setting of 0.001 means that the underlying security may be traded, for example, 123.1 or 123.12 or 123.123 butnot 123.1234. Validation Rules: 1 - 16 Numeric characters (Optional input) Details. When inputting trades the nominal amount entered must bemultiple of the value in this field. The exception to this is when 0 to 0.000001 is entered. In which case the nominal amount entered can have decimalamounts in accordance with the descriptions above. The default value for this field is 1.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The TradingUnits

      • getWeightedAvgLife

        public TField getWeightedAvgLife()
        Returns the WeightedAvgLife

        Field description: A numeric field indicating the number of years for the average life of the underlying instruments. The integerportion of this number represents the number of years and the decimal portion of the number is that portion of theyear. If this field is set, the system automatically recalculates the AVG.LIFE.MAT.DATE using the formula WEIGHTED.AVG.LIFE * 365 days + current date. For example, assume the weighted average is 1.16 and the current date is April 17, 2018. The average life maturity date is calculated as (1.16*365) = 423.4 This is then rounded to 423.This represents 423 days. The AVG.LIFE.MAT.DATE would then be calculated as April 17, 2018 + 423 which is Jun 14, 2015. This date should be greater than today and less than the MATURITY.DATE.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The WeightedAvgLife

        public void insertPriceQualMark(TField param, int pos)
        Insert the specified PriceQualMark to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This input for this field is determined in the application SM.PARAMETER, if the field PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is notSWIFT then the only valid input for this field is xd, otherwise the list of valid entries will be determined fromthe fields CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE in the same application. If the entry is xd then it indicates that the price quoted in the LAST.PRICE or DISC.YLD.PERC field isex-dividend. Otherwise it indicates the price condition, as specified by SWIFT, for example CDIV indicates the price is cumdividend, XWAR indicates the price is ex warrants. The user should consult the SWIFT manual for a full list ofprice conditions. Validation Rules: Input only allowed if the security price is updated manually otherwise this field is updated by the externalprice field. If PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is not SWIFT then the only permissible input is xd (Lowercase only - UPPERCASE not allowed) If PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is SWIFT then entry will be limited to values from CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE onSM.PARAMETER.

        Parameters:
        param - the PriceQualMark to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.

        Field description: This input for this field is determined in the application SM.PARAMETER, if the field PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is notSWIFT then the only valid input for this field is xd, otherwise the list of valid entries will be determined fromthe fields CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE in the same application. Otherwise it indicates the price condition, as specified by SWIFT, for example CDIV indicates the price is cumdividend, XWAR indicates the price is ex warrants. The user should consult the SWIFT manual for a full list ofprice conditions. Validation Rules: Input only allowed if the security price is updated manually otherwise this field is updated by the externalprice field.         Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Records the date from which accrued interest, coupons and dividends are payable (normally the issue date). Whenused in conjunction with the INT.PAYMENT.DATE field tells the System that Interest is to be calculated from accrualdate to payment date. This is effectively the last interest payment date. If the SUB.ASSET.TYPE relating to this record has its field KASSENOBLIGATIONEN set to YES then you may leave thisfield blank. In this case, when entering a SEC.TRADE, for example, you will be requested to enter the accrual startdate on the transaction yourself Validation Rules: Standard date format. (Optional input) If a value has been entered in the INT.PAYMENT.DATE field, then input is mandatory.

      • setAdjMarginRate

        public void setAdjMarginRate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for AdjMarginRate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used to specify the Adjusted margin rate for calculating ADJ.MARGIN.AMT in SC.POS.ASSET. Adjusted Margin Rate is used to calculate the Low Advanced Ratio for Collaterals to which the Portfolio/Asset isattached. Low Advance Ratio is the percentage of collateral that will be used for allocating to other currency liabilitiesduring collateral deficit calculation in Advance Collateral process. This field can either be used to specify the Low Advance Ratio for collateral LTV calculation or DiversifiedMargins for porfolios flagged for Diversification. If the flag "CO.MV.CHECK" in SC.PARAMETER is set to enable Preferential LTV functionality, Adj Marginwill be used only as Low Advance Ratio for collateral LTV calculations and will not be used for calculatingDiversified Margin. In this case ideally Adj Margin should be lesser than the Margin Rate. Thus an override will be raised if AdjMargin is greater than Preferential Margin Rate/Standard Margin Rate. a. If ADJ.MARGIN.RATE is used for diversification purpose and bank wants to use both concentration and portfoliodiversification functionality then, it will require a process change configurationso as to setup and use ADJ.MARGIN.RATE for concentration and PREFNTL.MARGIN.RATE for diversification and also set thefield CO.MV.CHECK in SC.PARAMETER as YES. b. If ADJ.MARGIN.RATE is used for concentration purpose and bank wants to use portfolio diversificationfunctionality then, it will require configuring field CO.MV.CHECK in SC.PARAMETER as YESand setup PREFNTL.MARGIN.RATE to be used for diversification. Validation Rules: Standard T24 Rate field with values ranging from 0 to 100.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setAmTradingUnits

        public void setAmTradingUnits(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for AmTradingUnits
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used by AM.MODELLING during Rebalance process. but in the event that the underlying security may be traded in fractions, then this field should be used tospecify the number of decimals permissable. 1 to indicate that only whole numbers are allowable. 0 to indicate any amount of decimals up to and including 6 (therefore same as 0.000001) 0.1 only one decimal permitted (can be none) 0.01 up to and including 2 decimals (none, 1 and 2) 0.001 up to and including 3 decimals (none, 1, 2 and 3) 0.0001 up to and including 4 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3 and 4) 0.00001 up to and including 5 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5) 0.000001 up to and including 6 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6) A setting of 0.001 means that the underlying security may be traded, for example, 123.1 or 123.12 or 123.123 butnot 123.1234. Validation Rules: Non Mandatory AM.TRADING.UNITS should be a Multiple of ODD.LOT.UNITS.

        Parameters:

      • setBrTradingUnits

        public void setBrTradingUnits(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for BrTradingUnits
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: It will be check on demand in the asset management modelling with the no file enquiry AM.SCE.PREVIEW.SOO . Specifies the smallest nominal amount that may be traded. Normally, for share type securities this will default to 1 but in the event that the underlying security may betraded in fractions, then this field should be used to specify the number of decimals permissible. 1 to indicate that only whole numbers are allowable. 0 to indicate any amount of decimals up to and including 6 (therefore same as 0.000001) 0.1 only one decimal permitted (can be none) 0.01 up to and including 2 decimals (none, 1 and 2) 0.001 up to and including 3 decimals (none, 1, 2 and 3) 0.0001 up to and including 4 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3 and 4) 0.00001 up to and including 5 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5) 0.000001 up to and including 6 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6) A setting of 0.001 means that the underlying security may be traded, for example, 123.1 or 123.12 or 123.123 butnot 123.1234. Validation Rules: Optional.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDayConvention

        public void setDayConvention(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for DayConvention
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Day convention to be used when calculating the Value Date for any corporate actions for this security. This isthe convention to be used when finding a working day in all the countries listed in the BUS.CENTRES field. This field will be used by the applications DIARY, DIV.COUP.DET, REDEMPTION.DET and STOCK.DIV.DET to calculate aworking day value date from the defaulted value date of the corporate actions event if this defaulted date is anon-working day in all the countries listed in the BUS.CENTRES field. Optional field. Any input must be FOLLOWING, MODIFIED or PRECEDING. These inputs have the following meanings; FOLLOWING The value date will be the first working day that follows the defaulted date. PRECEDING The value date will be the first working day that precedes the defaulted date. MODIFIED The value date will be the first working day that follows the defaulted day unless it falls in the nextcalendar month, in which case the value date will be the first working day that precedes the defaulted date. If this field is left blank then the value date used will be the defaulted date. Validation Rules: Optional input. Any input must be FOLLOWING, MODIFIED or PRECEDING.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setEntryLoadMethod

        public void setEntryLoadMethod(TField value)
        Set the specified value for EntryLoadMethod
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: The field identifies how the entry load is calculated and handled. There are different options as shown below:BID.OFFER - Denotes the entry load is factored into the NAV (Offer Price). Entry load need not be calculatedseparately.BANKPL - The entry load is calculated and only the net amount (after adjusting the entry load) is remitted to the fundhouse. The entry load will be booked to bank's PL.NETAMT - The fund house will calculate the entry load and allocate units for the net amount (subscription amount - entryload). The entry load may fully or partially be shared with the distributor separately. If Blank , then value will be defaulted from ENTRY.LOAD.METHOD in SC.STD.SEC.TRADE.The default method will beBANKPL Validation Rules: Allowed Values:BID.OFFER,NETAMT,BANKPL

      • setFifWeight

        public void setFifWeight(TField value)
        Set the specified value for FifWeight
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: The Foreign Inclusion Factor (FIF) of an instrument is a weighting assigned to an instrument that represents theproportion of shares outstanding that are deemed to be available for purchase in the public equity markets byinternational investors. In practice limitations on availability include: strategic and other shareholdings in an instrument limits on foreign ownership. The FIF is used by companies who compile indexes to provide a more accurate representation of company weightingin the index calculation. The contents of this field will be used by the AM.BENCH.INDICES application to provide amore accurate methodology of calculating indices. (NOT CURRENTLY DEVELOPED) A value between 0 and 1 should be entered.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setFifWeight

        public void setFifWeight(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for FifWeight
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: The Foreign Inclusion Factor (FIF) of an instrument is a weighting assigned to an instrument that represents theproportion of shares outstanding that are deemed to be available for purchase in the public equity markets byinternational investors. In practice limitations on availability include: strategic and other shareholdings in an instrument limits on foreign ownership. The FIF is used by companies who compile indexes to provide a more accurate representation of company weightingin the index calculation. The contents of this field will be used by the AM.BENCH.INDICES application to provide amore accurate methodology of calculating indices. (NOT CURRENTLY DEVELOPED) A value between 0 and 1 should be entered.

      • setGrp1Grp2Method

        public void setGrp1Grp2Method(TField value)
        Set the specified value for Grp1Grp2Method
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: The system calculates Group 1 holdings as at the start of the Equalisation Period (date of last unit trustdistribution). All purchases from this date up until the end of the equalization period (ex-date) will be classedas Group 2 holdings. This field dictates which Group (1 or 2) sales will be deducted from during the Equalisation Period. null - The SUMLIFO option is used FIFO - Uses the First In/First Out calculation for sales LIFO - Uses Last In /First Out calculation for sales SUMLIFO - Sums all the purchases sales then performs Last In/First Out Calculation for the result DEFAULT - Copies the default setting from the SUB.ASSET.TYPE record Validation Rules: LIFO, FIFO, SUMLIFO or DEFAULT Examples 1. In this example the first transaction we have is a sale followed by a purchase. FIFO This method will try reduce the Group 1 units first but if there is not enough Group 1 units, the remainder willbe taken from Group 2 units.

        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000 0 8,000
        Purchase5,000 8,000 5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 6,500 5,000 11,500
        Total 6,500 5,000 11,500
        LIFO This method will try reduce the Group 2 units first but if there is not enough Group 2 units, the remainder willbe taken from Group 1 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000 0 8,000
        Purchase5,000 8,000 5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 8,000 3,500 11,500
        Total 8,000 3,500 11,500
        SUMLIFO This method will sum all the purchase sales for the Equalisation Period then try to reduce the Group 2 unitsfirst but if there is not enough Group 2 units, the remainder will be taken from Group 1 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000
        Purchase5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 11,500
        Total(1,500) 10,000 1,500 11,500
        2. In this example the first transaction is a purchase followed by two sales. This method will try reduce the Group 1 units first but if there is not enough Group 1 units, the remainder willbe taken from Group 2 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Purchase5,000 10,000 5,000 15,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000 5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 6,500 5,000 11,500
        Total 6,500 5,000 11,500
        LIFO This method will try reduce the Group 2 units first but if there is not enough Group 2 units, the remainder willbe taken from Group 1 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Purchase5,000 10,000 5,000 15,000
        Sale-2,000 10,000 3,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 10,000 1,500 11,500
        Total 10,000 1,500 11,500
        SUMLIFO This method will sum all the purchase sales for the Equalisation Period then try to reduce the Group 2 unitsfirst but if there is not enough Group 2 units, the remainder will be taken from Group 1 units.
        EventTransactionsGroup 1 UnitsGroup 2 UnitsTotal Units
        Last Distribution10,000 0 10,000
        Sale-2,000 8,000
        Purchase5,000 13,000
        Sale-1,500 11,500
        Total(1,500) 10,000 1,500 11,500

        nothing

        public void setISIN(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for ISIN
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: International security identification number. Can be specified as an alternate index. The level of duplication, if any, for this field is specified in the SM.PARAMETER application. Validation Rules: 1-12 Alphanumeric characters. (Optional input) First two characters must be alpha characters for the Country code, No validation against the country table inT24. The next nine characters must be alpha-numeric for the National Security Number. The last one is a check digit from 0 to 9, which will be validated against Modulus 10 Double Add DoubleAlgorithm. This field get validated only when ISIN.VALIDATION field in SC.PARAMETER is set to YES.

        Parameters:

        Returns:

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the date on which the 1st interest payment or coupon falls due. If the future date is not known thenenter the last date interest was paid. The system will calculate the next payment date in conjunction withNO.OF.PAYMENTS at the authorisation level of the dividend payment record. This is effectively the Next Interest Payment date. If the SUB.ASSET.TYPE relating to this record has its field KASSENOBLIGATIONEN set to YES then you may leave thisfield blank. In this case, when entering a SEC.TRADE, for example, you will be requested to enter the next interestpayment date on the transaction yourself. Validation Rules: Standard date format. If the INTEREST.RATE field has a value then this field becomes a mandatory input EXCEPT when the security'sSUB.ASSET.TYPE field KASSENOBLIGATIONEN is set to YES. Must not be after the maturity date.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setInterestDayBasis

        public void setInterestDayBasis(TField value)
        Set the specified value for InterestDayBasis
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Defines the method of calculation for accrued interest on a Security be it a Bond, Gilt, Loan stock etc. Example: A = 360/360 where a standard 30 day month is assumed over 360 days a year, as is the case for allEurobond calculations. Note that O and U values are intended to enable the setting-up of French Oat and US Treasury Bills respectively. For US Treasury (value = U), the number of days in the denominator vary according to the number of days in theinterest period. For example, if the number of days in the interest period is 182 and the number of payments in ayear is 2, then the denominator (i.e. basis days) would be 364. Similarly, if number of days in a interest periodis 184, the base days would be 368. For a basic fixed interest French Oat (value = O) and also for French BTAN issues, the process requires roundingwithin the calculation to the nearest THIRD decimal (0.0005 is rounded up) For example : An investor holds 10 000 securities of the 5.25%, 25 April 2008, OAT. Full coupon per security: 0.05250 payable on 25 April 2000 Accrued interest calculation date: 24 March 2000 Number of days accrued: 334 Total number of days in the interest period: 366 (the O is actually hard-coded as ACT/ACT basis) Calculation : 5.25 * 334 / 366 = 4.790834 rounded to 3 decimals = 4.791 Therefore : Accrued interest in percentage: 4.791% Total amount of accrued interest paid in euro: 479.10 NOTE : Please refer to the BOND.ROUNDING field on this file, the two files UNIT.INT.METHOD and BOND.ROUNDING to enablegreater control over rounding of interest. Your User Guide explains the processes in greater detail to help youdecide. Validation Rules: Alphabetic character. (Optional input) If BOND.OR.SHARE is B input is mandatory, regardless of whether an interest rate is specified. If left blank anunreliable yield figure will be calculated. If BOND.OR.SHARE is S input is not allowed. Only A, B, C, D, E, F, G, O or U can be entered into this field. If G is entered then the NO.OF.PAYMENTS field must be either 1, 2, 4, 13, 26 or 52.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setPrefntlMarginRate

        public void setPrefntlMarginRate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for PrefntlMarginRate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the enhanced margin rate that will override any standard margin (MARGIN.RATE) applicable for portfoliosflagged for Diversification. Validation Rules: Standard T24 Rate field. This field is allowed for input only when "CO.MV.CHECK" flag in SC.PARAMETER is set that enables thePreferential LTV functionality. Value can be specified as an absolute value ranging from 0 to 100 or as a variance with "+" sign. A variance indicates the incremental value to be added to the Standrad Margin Rate to arrive at the enhancedrate. Thus Margin Rate becomes mandatory if Preferential Rate is defined as a variance. The sum of Preferential Rate defined as a variance and Standard Margin Rate cannot exceed 100. Ideally Preferential Rate should always be greater than the Standard Margin Rate. Thus an override will be raisedif the Preferential Rate defined as an absolute value is lesser than the Standard Margin Rate. The hierarchy in which the Preferential Rate will be considered is the same as existing margin rate determinationhierarchy.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setPriceQualMark

        public void setPriceQualMark(java.lang.CharSequence param, int idx)
        Set the specified PriceQualMark to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This input for this field is determined in the application SM.PARAMETER, if the field PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is notSWIFT then the only valid input for this field is xd, otherwise the list of valid entries will be determined fromthe fields CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE in the same application. If the entry is xd then it indicates that the price quoted in the LAST.PRICE or DISC.YLD.PERC field isex-dividend. Otherwise it indicates the price condition, as specified by SWIFT, for example CDIV indicates the price is cumdividend, XWAR indicates the price is ex warrants. The user should consult the SWIFT manual for a full list ofprice conditions. Validation Rules: Input only allowed if the security price is updated manually otherwise this field is updated by the externalprice field. If PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is not SWIFT then the only permissible input is xd (Lowercase only - UPPERCASE not allowed) If PRICE.QUAL.FORMAT is SWIFT then entry will be limited to values from CUM.INDICATE and EX.INDICATE onSM.PARAMETER.

        Parameters:
        param - the PriceQualMark to append
        idx - the position in collection
        Returns:
        nothing

        public void setSecStatus(TField value)
        Set the specified value for SecStatus
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: DEF - Defaulted ,mainly for bonds where coupon payment is defaulted. Trading can still continue. No overridemessage or hard block by the system DEL - Delisted ,when security is delisted from exchange, it is also expired and no more trading can be done for this security. System will raise an override message, validating against the status date for any transactionson or after the status date SUS - Suspended , when security is suspended with an effective date, no more trading is allowed. System should provide an override message, validating against the status date for any transactions on or after thestatus date. NON.TRADABLE - When security is Non Tradable with an effective date, no more trading is allowed. System should provide an override message, validating against the status date for any transactions on or after thestatus date. Validation Rules Allowed Values are DEF,DEL and SUS

      • setSubAmtAdj

        public void setSubAmtAdj(TField value)
        Set the specified value for SubAmtAdj
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: In cases where rebate or discount is offered on the entry load, this field determines whether the clientinvestment (subscription amount) will be retained or reduced based on the rebate/discount offered. If the field is No or blank, the original subscription amount will be retained (by grossing up the investmentamount) and client will be debited for the same after applying the rebate (and channel discount) on entry load. If set to YES, the subscription amount will be reduced in line with rebate/channel discount. The field atSECURITY.MASTER level will override the company level setting. Validation Rules: Allowed Values:YES, NO or blank

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setTradingUnits

        public void setTradingUnits(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for TradingUnits
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the smallest nominal amount that may be traded. Normally, for share type securities this will default to 1 but in the event that the underlying security may betraded in fractions, then this field should be used to specify the number of decimals permissable. 1 to indicate that only whole numbers are allowable. 0 to indicate any amount of decimals up to and including 6 (therefore same as 0.000001) 0.1 only one decimal permitted (can be none) 0.01 up to and including 2 decimals (none, 1 and 2) 0.001 up to and including 3 decimals (none, 1, 2 and 3) 0.0001 up to and including 4 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3 and 4) 0.00001 up to and including 5 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5) 0.000001 up to and including 6 decimals (none, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6) A setting of 0.001 means that the underlying security may be traded, for example, 123.1 or 123.12 or 123.123 butnot 123.1234. Validation Rules: 1 - 16 Numeric characters (Optional input) Details. When inputting trades the nominal amount entered must bemultiple of the value in this field. The exception to this is when 0 to 0.000001 is entered. In which case the nominal amount entered can have decimalamounts in accordance with the descriptions above. The default value for this field is 1.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        public void setUnpaidAmount(java.lang.CharSequence value)

        Field description: Field used for Part Paid securities where the amount that is unpaid is included in the price. Validation Rules: Numeric input only, if the PRICE.TYPE attached to the security is a percentage price, then can only be in therange 0 to 100 Must be less than the value in the LAST.PRICE field. Can not be changed after the security has been traded.

      • setWeightedAvgLife

        public void setWeightedAvgLife(TField value)
        Set the specified value for WeightedAvgLife
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: A numeric field indicating the number of years for the average life of the underlying instruments. The integerportion of this number represents the number of years and the decimal portion of the number is that portion of theyear. If this field is set, the system automatically recalculates the AVG.LIFE.MAT.DATE using the formula WEIGHTED.AVG.LIFE * 365 days + current date. For example, assume the weighted average is 1.16 and the current date is April 17, 2018. The average life maturity date is calculated as (1.16*365) = 423.4 This is then rounded to 423.This represents 423 days. The AVG.LIFE.MAT.DATE would then be calculated as April 17, 2018 + 423 which is Jun 14, 2015. This date should be greater than today and less than the MATURITY.DATE.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing
